icProfile?language=EN>shallandra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/7/02 11:14:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1669.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 70 Expansion?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Do you realize how trivial things would be if we could level to 70?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, this problem was encountered with Kunark.  Verant implemented banishment.  ALL &quot;boss&quot; mobs could be made to have permissable level limits.  If a character exceeds this limit, they get banished.  In example:<br>
<br>
Vulak'Aerr shouts, &quot;Immortals are not welcome here, Shallandra.  Leave NOW!!&quot;<br>
<br>
LOADING... PLEASE WAIT.<br>
<br>
That would solve the problem with trivial encounters and force a player to decide if being Immortal is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> really</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> worth it, as it would prevent them from doing lower end encounters.<br>
<br>
This could have one positive aspect: Once uber guilds decide to go planar, it opens up their old stomping grounds to other guilds.  This could free up some contested zones (i.e. NToV).<br>
<br>
Another thing to consider is skill caps.  Due to memory constraints, server side, skills will never cap above 252.  Thus, characters would have to improve in other avenues.  Melee could get attack bonuses and higher combat tables.  Casters get new spells.  All classes could unlock new AXP skills as they level.  For example, with monks:<br>
<br>
Level 61:<br>
* Double Kick 1:  Character has a 10% chance to double attack when performing a flying kick or other special attack. (4 AXP)<br>
<br>
Level 62:<br>
* Rapid Mend 1:  Decreases the refresh timer on the mend skill by 10% (4 AXP)<br>
<br>
Level 63:<br>
* Fearless: The monk is immune to all fear effects.  (6 AXP)<br>
<br>
Level 64:<br>
* Double Kick 2:  Character has a 25% chance to double attack when performing a flying kick or other special attack. (8 AXP)<br>
<br>
Level 65<br>
* Feign Mastery: Feign simply <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> cannot</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> fail, due to a skill check.  Does not prevent interrupts from spells or other effects.  (15 AXP)<br>
* Rapid Mend 2: Reduces the refresh timer on mend by 25%. (8 AXP)<br>
<br>
Level 66:<br>
* Pain Touch:  Eagle strike has a chance to stun a target (short duration).  (12 AXP)<br>
<br>
Level 67:<br>
* Double Kick 3:  Character has a 50% chance to double attack when performing a flying kick or other special attack. (12 AXP)<br>
* Rapid Mend 3: Reduces the refresh on mend by 50% (12 AXP)<br>
<br>
Level 69:<br>
* Celestial Awareness;  Character has no AC penalty to attacks made at his flank.  Furthermore, the character can block, dodge, and riposte attacks from ANY assailant, regardless of the direction from which the attack comes.  (12 AXP)<br>
<br>
Level 70:<br>
* Celestial Harmony: The monk has the chance to quadruple attack with the primary hand.  (15 AXP)<br>
* Celestial Affinity: The monk cannot be slowed OR hastened by any means, except those means invoked by the monk himself.  (15 AXP)<br>
* Mastery of Body: Character has the ability to imbue himself with 70% spell haste. (15 AXP)<br>
* Mastery of Mind: Character cannot be mezzed, stunned, charmed, or affected by any mind altering spells.  (15 AXP)<br>
* Mastery of Spirit: The next mend will completely heal the monk.  Reuse: 72 minutes (1 game day).  (15 AXP)<br>
<br>
Those are things that I can see an enlightened monk being able to do (but currently can't).  Another skill that could be interesting, for warriors, is beserking.<br>
<br>
* Beserking:  Warrior (and others) are no longer aware of the warriors current health status.  The warrior will not fall until the beserker rage ends.  Duration 1 minutes.  Reuse: 72 minutes (1 game day).  (15 AXP)<br>
<br>
Would be extremely interesting if, like Rugen said, some of the planar zones were PvP.  This could make people re-evaluate the way the game is played, come up with new strategies, etc.<br>
<br>
I mean just imagine the thrill--and horror--of a beserking dwarf bashing away with an axe, oblivious to the spells and hits landing on him.  On the other side of the line you have a celestial monk fighting off 4 warriors, blocking attacks from every side, doing his best to emerge victorious.<br>
<br>
Ah... reminds me of good fiction <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As for PvP... the next expansion could use this really bad.  I hadn't even considered that much, but just having a couple of zones (sort of middle-grounds between the plains) where PCs could do battle--basically zone-wide arenas--would be awesome. <p>Shallandra McKnight, Uba Monkey<br>
Zassazy Moonkiepett, Sexy Leezard Shaman<br>
Daxes Solvaires, Naughty Flute Girl<br>
Daemonica, Evil Daughter of Innoruuk<br>
<br>
